      "name": "Rich text article",
      "settings": {
        "rta_subtitle": "",
        "rta_h1title": "",
        "rta_title": "",
        "rta_text1": "<p>A spectacular start for the Grand Soleil Cup 2025: the <strong>first leg </strong>has officially wrapped up in <strong>Cala Galera</strong>, from <strong>May 23rd to 25th</strong>, in collaboration with the <strong>Circolo Nautico e della Vela Argentario </strong>and the <strong>Marina di Cala Galera</strong>.<br><br>Around 40 Grand Soleil yachts took part in this opening event, confirming the international spirit of the regatta, with owners and crews coming from Italy, France, the Netherlands, Canada, Australia, and Japan.<br><br>The weekend kicked off with a welcome cocktail on the CNVA terrace, followed on Saturday by a coastal sail towards Giannutri with winds building up to 20 knots. On Sunday, ideal conditions allowed for a technical race around the buoys. The event wrapped up with an award ceremony and a celebratory toast on the dock.<br><br>The <strong>overall winner was Luduan 2.0, a Grand Soleil 48 owned by Enrico De Crescenzo</strong>, who took first place in the All Sails category. The spotlight was also on the new LINEA PLUS, represented on the water by four of the most recent and innovative models in the range—proof of Cantiere del Pardo’s ongoing commitment to product evolution.<br><br>A heartfelt thank you to all the owners, crews, and main sponsors for making this first leg of the Grand Soleil Cup 2025 truly special.</p>",
        "rta-cta_label": "DISCOVER THE HIGHLIGHTS",
        "rta-cta_link": "shopify://blogs/news/grand-soleil-cup-2025-cala-galera-three-unforgettable-days-of-sailing-sun-and-passion",
        "rta_modal_label": "",
        "rta_modal_id": "",
        "alignment_mobile": "left",
        "alignment_desktop": "center",
        "pt_mobile": 40,
